## NON-NEGOTIABLE OPERATING RULES

### Rule 1: The Concept is the Site
Do not design a standard page layout then add 3D elements or animations. The concept and the execution must be a single cohesive entity. Ask: "What if the interface and the experience were the same thing?"

### Rule 2: Find Your One Signature Technique
Every project needs one visual fingerprint that makes it identifiable in a screenshot without a logo. Examples:
* Text duplication on hover (RXK style).
* Cursor that physically displaces nearby layout typography.
* WebGL displacement that reacts directly to cursor velocity.
* Images that only fully resolve when cursor rests on them.

### Rule 3: Motion is Physics, Not Just Easing
Good animations use basic easing functions. Elite animations use spring physics, overshoot on entries, lag interpolation on cursor paths (lerp factor 0.08-0.12), and velocity-based scaling.

### Rule 4: Sound Elevates Everything
Interactive audio design (hover clicks, transition sweeps, ambient loops) is mandatory. Use Howler.js. Audio must start muted by default, with a visible, satisfying mute toggle.

### Rule 5: The Loader is Designed Content
Never show a generic loading spinner. The load screen is the first impression. Use it to display progress counters, award badges, or setup hints.

### Rule 6: Physics When Possible
Use Rapier.js for WASM-based 3D physics or Matter.js for 2D. Even without full simulations, apply spring models to UI elements (draggable components, elastic hover responses, inertia-driven cards).

### Rule 7: Collaboration Credits are Part of the Work
Standardize credit attribution: "Design by [Name] / Development by [Name] / WebGL by [Name]". Separates developer and designer tokens cleanly.

### Rule 8: Desktop-First Bias for Immersive Creative Work
For high-concept portfolios, agency sites, and brand launches, desktop is primary. Mobile serves as a simplified, graceful degradation pathway. For B2B products and SaaS, mobile remains primary.

### Rule 9: HSL Color System, Obsidian Bias
Default to dark-first styling (`#171717`, `#0a0a0a`) on creative layouts. Define all colors using Hue, Saturation, and Lightness (HSL) variables. Use a single accent color per project.

### Rule 10: Performance is Respect
First Contentful Paint (FCP) must remain under 0.8s, and frame rates must maintain a stable 60fps. Utilize lazy loading, dynamic imports, and capacity checks.

